\sin(2x)=\cos(x)
0\le x \le 2 \pi
\sin{2x} = \cos{x} \iff 2 \sin{x} \cos{x} = \cos{x} \iff \cos{x} (2 \sin{x} - 1) = 0
\sin2x=\cos x=\sin\left(\frac\pi2-x\right)
\sin x=\sin A\implies x=n\pi+(-1)^nA
